data: With the fifth and final Singh child on its way, Hemani demands that they need a larger house in order to have more room and not be so crowded. The entire family does not like the idea, especially Avatar. Meanwhile, Dolly and Aayan audition to have the opportunity to work in an indoor show about Romeo and Juliet. Since Sunny is finally leaving, Rolli Aunty could not be happier. They pull ultimate pranks on each other to see who gets the last laugh. In the end when the family is almost done packing, Hemani goes back inside because she thought she had forgot something. When she goes inside, she remembers all of the memories that her and the family had at the house. Then she tells Avatar that she wants the family to stay at the house.

Ever since Dolly and Aayan are together, the basketball team has not been able to win a game. This leads to everybody thinking that Dolly is Bad Luck. So they fake breakup, which will help the team relax, thinking the curse has been lifted, they will win and then get back together. Meanwhile, overhearing that Hemani and Avatar were talking about how the son of Hemani's friend was going to send him to Boarding school, but Sunny thinks they were talking about him so he starts acting on his best behaviour. When Hemani and Avatar found out they continue to let him believe he's being sent to Boarding school.

Since Dolly is going to her graduation party, Hemani doesn't let dolly go anywhere without Rohan. Dolly has a plan that she will tell Hemani that she's going to Pam's home to study, but when she goes to the graduation party, she changes her dress. Meanwhile, Rohan needs a partner for his graduation party, so when the pizza delivery girl, shows up he becomes attracted to her and they go on a date. She asks him to her graduation party, Rohan accepts. Unfortunately she is homeschooled and the party is in her basement. After going to the doctor and getting an news about the gender of the baby, Hemani does not want to know the gender of the baby until it is actually born. On the other hand, Avatar is anxious to know, so he heard the doctor's say that the "singhs" are going to have triplets. But they were actually talking about the other singhs!

Hemani overhears Dolly and Aayan talking about through the baby monitor and follows them; Hemani is shocked when she blows their cover. Dolly did not want to tell her because Hemani hogs the spotlight. In the end, Hemani fills in for one of the cast members due to him breaking his leg. Meanwhile, Avatar wants to fix a switch in the cage of a gorilla at the zoo and he's desperate to prove Sunny that he is cool. Plus, he also to one-up Quint, an Zoo Keeper.

data: Six months ago, Emmet Cole, adventurer and host of The Undiscovered Country, disappeared while on an expedition deep in the uncharted waters of the Amazon River. The fruitless search and subsequent 'memorial service' left thousands of fans in shock at the loss of their icon. Now, his emergency beacon had been activated, and his wife Tess, who reluctantly faced reality, organizes a search party to find him. The team comprises her estranged son Lincoln, who was more than ready to leave the past behind; Emmet's long-time friend and Undiscovered Country producer Clark Quietly; Magus mechanic Emilio Valenzuela and his daughter Jahel; Lena Landry, daughter of cameraman Russ Landry who has disappeared along with Cole; and Captain Kurt Bryndilson, protector of the expedition. What the team doesn't know is that this journey will take them to a place where magic comes alive and things are never what they seem. The paranormal entity they encountered in this episode is a corpo seco.

When Jahel becomes possessed by Emmet Cole's spirit, Tess becomes undeterred from her goal of finding clues to her husband's whereabouts. The team then discovers a tree draped in children's dolls, and an old legend reminds them that the tree of dolls is an offering site to "La Dejada, the abandoned one", as mentioned by Lena, in this case a spirit of a girl who drowned in the river. Tess was suddenly dragged away to drown and Lincoln has to find a way to appease the spirit.

When the "Magus" crew got a clue that Dr Emmet Cole might have been to a tree cave nearby, they followed that lead that needs them to hike through the forest jungle. They found out that they have entered the Morcegos territory, a tribe of warriors, of which they are known to be "The Guardians of the Forest", they are there to judge if the visitors are worthy to pass or not. When the team entered the cave; except for camera man AJ, who has a trauma with caves, they accidentally disturbed the bats dwelling inside. Later that night, they were visited by the Morcegos who placed markings around their tents and infected the eyes of the individuals who went inside the tree cave with some kind of a toxin, one by one they lose their sights. Camera operator AJ Poulain must find a cure and face his fear before the team becomes blind permanently.

Soon, this discovered curse becomes a matter of life and death, not just for Jonas, but for the rest of the crew as well. When the others plan to jettison Jonas and continue the mission, Lincoln must face this challenge and be the moral compass.

After finding Emmet's camera bag during a trek to the Sahte Falls, the Magus crew examines the tapes and finds footage of Emmet, with two of his crew members looking for "The Source"; a tribe living in the jungle who have powers to heal or achieve anything. As a mysterious demon follows them, killing one of the crew members that leaves the other one in shock that she decides to leave, Emmet is left by himself. In the jungle, he realises that he might have made a mistake coming out here. As he progresses through the jungle alone, hungry and weak, the mysterious demon follows him, and as it is about to take Emmet's life, tribesmen come and save him. They heal him, and take him to a research facility in the jungle, before hurrying off. People from the base see Emmet and rush towards him to help. The Magus crew realise that he is alive and trek the jungle to find the facility, only to discover it is abandoned.

Beginning where the previous episode ends—Emmet Cole's last known location—the research facility, the Magus crew not only discovers that it is abandoned, but also that there has been illegal research and experiments occurring, with the inhabitants of the forest being used as test subjects. The research went wrong and turned the inhabitants and workers into cannibals who begin to stalk the crew. One of the researchers-turned-zombie is Kurt Brynildson's former German fiancée and the reason for his secrecy is finally revealed. The crew finds "Rabbit", who abandoned Cole some months prior to the episode, and also discover a room in the facility with an unconscious Emmet Cole concealed in a cocoon. They cut him out and travel back to the ship, only to be followed by the cannibals, which results in the death of one of their crew and Emmet Cole waking up.

After Lincoln is shot dead by a member of the Magus, Jahel disobeys her father and Emmet by calling upon the river's spirit for help. With the help of Tess, Jahel performs a ritual which brings Lincoln back to life. Lincoln tells the crew that Kurt shot him, when later it is revealed to be Jonas. With an evil spirit inside him, Lincoln kills Jonas. Clark discovers Jonas' body and the crew realize the truth about what is happening—the Boiuna's spirit is living inside Lincoln. Emmet asks Lena to help force the evil spirit out of his son and they perform an exorcism. When it doesn't work, Emmet asks Kurt to help, who tells him that he needs to talk to his son, not the spirit. Emmet does so, which results in the spirit leaving. The crew then tries to follow the map out of the Boiuna to a fishing village for supplies, but find that it isn't there when they arrive. Clark sends up the heli-cam to inspect the surroundings. On a monitor, the crew sees that the river and terrain are changing, to which Lincoln explains that the Boiuna won't let them leave.

table-0938-404.caption: Previous forensic experts
data: Forensic experts in the earliest cases

The first forensic doctor was never called by his name and was known as Dr. Saheb. In the first episode of C.I.D., there were two forensics doctors, one for autopsies and the other for toxicology. After that, there was a doctor, who stayed there for a considerable amount of time before Dr. Verma arrived. The doctor before him had scrawny eyes, thick glasses and was almost bald. He had a French cut beard and he was of medium height and weight. In the third period of Dr. Salunkhe (2007–present), a dumb doctor arrived who was also unknown.

She was a widow of a senior cop. She thought ACP Pradyuman was the killer of her husband but was proved wrong. Later, she proved to be an able forensic doctor and helped the team a lot. She placed a lot of faith in ACP Pradyuman, after he was proven innocent.
She was a brilliant doctor and was often lauded by the team for her efforts. Daya had a minor crush on her.

table-0938-401.caption: : Officers
data: He was a replacement to Inspector Viren (Ashutosh Gowarikor). He joined the C.I.D team since the episode "The Case of the Stolen Dynamite" in June, 1999 as an Inspector. His character is portrayed to be smart, suave, intellectual, intensive yet vulnerable. He has suffered brain trauma in an earlier case. As a result, he has suffered permanent episodic memory loss, getting occasional flashbacks and amnesia episodes (this problem has been a major source of trouble to him and the team many a times). His mother passed away three months post this incident. There are still a lot of speculations about his past and the people in his life before his memory loss. He is best friends with fellow Senior Inspector, Daya. They are just made for each other. He is in a relationship with Forensic Expert Dr. Tarika and often tries to flirt with her. The rest of the C.I.D. team often tease him because of the way he acts around her. He is known for his intelligence and shooting skills. Abhijeet is one of the most popular characters in the series. He is the most bravest, honest and intelligent officer.

He joined the C.I.D. team since the episode "The Case of Cross Connection" in 1999. He is one of the main characters in the series. He is a strong and smart officer. He is often seen (and famous for) breaking doors whenever a situation demands it. He is a strong and tough cop, yet a gentle person. He is best friends with Senior Inspector Abhijeet, and he trusts him the most. His other close friends are ACP Pradyuman, Inspector Purvi and Inspector Shreya. Shreya has a major crush on him and has tried to tell her feelings to Daya indirectly and also has tried to share her all feelings. He is also falling in love with Shreya.
He was introduced in the episode "Khooni Paani". He is a very intelligent and brave officer of the C.I.D. team.
He is a capable and hardworking officer of the C.I.D. team. Daya is Nikhil's guru and Nikhil wishes to be like him.

She is one of the bravest C.I.D. officers. she was first introduced in the episode "Raaz Sar Aur Haath Ka", alongside Sub-Inspector Vineet (2012 - 2013). She is one of the bravest C.I.D. officers. She is in love with Senior Inspector Daya and she always admires him and wishes to marry him and get teased by other mates.
He is an another comedian of the show, besides Fredricks. He finds jokes and humour in the most serious cases, and that is the reason why ACP Pradyuman always scolds him and Pankaj is afraid of him.
He is also an another comedian of the C.I.D. team, besides Fredricks and Pankaj. However, his appearances are occasional in the show.

data: His First case was "Case Of Thief Within"
Regarded as one of the best female C.I.D officers and stayed with team for a long period of time.
Was the replacement for Inspector Viren
He was a silent figure and a good friend of Fredricks. He left C.I.D in late 2005.

Originally joined C.I.D. to find out the murderer of his brother. He cheated C.I.D. by revealing secrets to Nakul (ACP's criminal son) for the sake of money. Shot by ACP and then died in hospital ward due to the poisonous gas released by Nakul.

She was an intelligent and brave officer although her sister was a big criminal. She did not have friendly relations with Abhijeet because she proved that he was present at a murder spot. Died in the episode "Mad Bomber" (August 12–19, 2005). She was first stabbed and then died due to an explosion.

She was extremely headstrong and often took matters into her own hands. During the episodes of "Faceoff" (October 21, 2005 – November 11, 2005) and "Trail In London" (November 18, 2005 – December 2, 2005) she suspected ACP Pradyuman was a killer.
He joined the Team as a Sub Inspector, after a few years he was promoted to an Inspector, He was good friends with Freddricks (Freddy). He also liked Officer Tasha

She was one of the best woman officers and very smart. However, when Devyana joined C.I.D., she began to feel insecure. She was mean to Devyana and always tried to ridicule her and take credit for her work. Transferred.
Appeared in one episode, "Murder in the Safety Vault" (May 12, 2006) and took Daya's replacement.

Debuted in the case "The Don's Final Revenge" (August 10, 2007). ACP Pradyuman was very rude to her because he thought she was incapable. In "The Case of Dr. O's Mysterious Treasure" (August 31, 2007), he wanted to transfer her because of her belief in superstition and her friendship with Madam Zara, a psychic reader who was disliked by Pradyuman. She initially was the weakest C.I.D. officer and was scared of blood and corpses. However, with her brilliant detective skills, she overcame her fear. She was instrumental in catching the criminal in "Bhoot Bangala" (February 8, 2008).

Debuted in the episode "Khoon Bhari Holi" (March 21, 2008). Initially, she followed C.I.D. officers about in this episode and revealed her identity as a C.I.D. member in the next episode. She got on well with Kaveri.

She debuted in the case "Khoon Bhari Holi" (March 21, 2008) along with fellow C.I.D. officer Lavanya. She was very humane and got emotional very often. ACP Pradyuman ridiculed her and Lavanya for this in "Katil Kaun Dohri Uljhan" (March 28, 2008).

First appeared in the case "Khoon Ka Raaj... Ek Aawaz" (May 29, 2009). She was not allowed to join the team because drugs were found in her bag, of which she was unaware. Later, ACP tested the drugs and found that they were not original. She is a very brilliant,honest and very clever and has an intuition to figuring out how crimes may have been caused. She is killed in the line of duty in the episode "Khatre Mein Tasha" (December 4, 2010). She breaths her last in the hospital, surrounded by her team.she is the best female officer after asha.

Debuted in the episode "Maut Ka Aashirwad" (May 14, 2010). At first, she was not allowed to join because her brother Rahul was suspected to be a criminal because everyone thought that he added poison on the ashes of the blessing; he was proven innocent. She was a good friend of tasha and purvi.

table-0938-490.caption: Season 2 (2012)
data: It's Nikki's second birthday and the family wants to give her the birthday of a lifetime. Avatar's idea of giving Nikki a pony ride goes haywire when he rents a pony which gets stolen. Nikki's love for Super Sabzi (a popular children TV show) gives Dolly the idea to buy tickets to their next concert. But to their dismay, the concert sells out before they can get tickets. They then try to win tickets by entering a video contest, but end up losing. They do everything they can to get tickets. Meanwhile, Rohan tries to sell one of his songs to one of the TV show actor. As a result, they all end up in jail, but surprisingly, one of the TV show actor sings one of Rohan's songs to the other TV show actor. He sells the song, and uses the money to get the Singhs out of jail.

Dolly falls for a guy named Gaurav who she finds is interested in Aliens vs. Animals, a fantasy card game for boys like Sunny. So, she pretends to like Aliens vs. Animals to impress Gaurav and he makes her play a game of L.A.R.P. out in public with him and his friends, which turns out to be another one of his hobbies. Meanwhile, Nikki pokes Hemani in the eye and she pretends to be hurt to stay in the hospital longer so she does not have to take care of the kids. data: When Hemani Singh returns to work as a nurse, she tells her family to stay at home, but is obviously worried about her husband Avatar's ability to take care of their baby daughter Nikki. Avatar assures her everything will be fine at home and her teenage daughter Dolly, who's study date at the library is canceled because of this, goes against Hemani's wishes and invites her date Ritesh to come to their house. Dolly gets distracted by him, and Ritesh repeatedly try to tell Dolly his feelings, but the Singh family members keep interrupting. Her older brother Rohan is trying to have a jam session with his best friend Popi (Yash Mittal) and her younger brother Sunny is feeling as if everyone is forgetting about him and goes to Mrs. Roli's house eating her food. Meanwhile, Avatar slips and falls down the stairs and Dolly has to take care of Nikki while Rohan drives Avatar to the hospital.
